  .instructions(data-platform="iphone")
    ol
      li From your iPhone‚Äôs home screen, open the <strong>Settings</strong> app.
      li Tap <strong>Wi-Fi</strong>, then tap your preferred network in the list.
      li Tap <strong>Configure DNS</strong>, then tap <strong>Manual</strong>.
      li If there are any existing entries, tap the <strong>-</strong> button, and <strong>Delete</strong> next to each one.
      li Tap the <strong>+ Add Server</strong> button, then type <strong>1.1.1.1</strong>
      li Tap the <strong>+ Add Server</strong> button again, then type <strong>1.0.0.1</strong>.
      li Tap the <strong>+ Add Server</strong> button again, then type <strong>2606:4700:4700::1111</strong>.
      li Tap the <strong>+ Add Server</strong> button again, then type <strong>2606:4700:4700::1001</strong>.
      li Tap the <strong>Save</strong> button on the top right.
      li You‚Äôre all set! Your device now has faster, more private DNS servers üöÄ

  .instructions(data-platform="linux")
    p
      | While these steps are for Ubuntu, most Linux distributions configure DNS settings through the Network Manager.
      | Alternatively, your DNS settings can be specified in <code class="inline">/etc/resolv.conf</code>

    ol
      li Click the Applications <i class="fas fa-th"></i> icon on the left menu bar.
      li Click <strong>Settings</strong>, then <strong>Network</strong>.
      li Find your internet connection on the right pane, then click the gear <i class="fas fa-cog"></i> icon.
      li Click the <strong>IPv4</strong> or <strong>IPv6</strong> tab to view your DNS settings.
      li Set the ‚ÄúAutomatic‚Äù toggle on the DNS entry to <strong>Off</strong>.
      li
        span Provide the 1.1.1.1 DNS addresses in the DNS entries field:
        ul
          li For IPv4: <strong>1.1.1.1,1.0.0.1</strong>
          li For IPv6: <strong>2606:4700:4700::1111,2606:4700:4700::1001</strong>
      li Click <strong>Apply</strong>, then restart your browser.
      li You‚Äôre all set! Your device now has faster, more private DNS servers üöÄ

  .instructions(data-platform="windows")
    ol
      li Click on the Start menu, then click on <strong>Control Panel</strong>.
      li Click on <strong>Network and Internet</strong>.
      li Click on <strong>Change Adapter Settings</strong>.
      li Right click on the Wi-Fi network you are connected to, then click <strong>Properties</strong>.
      li Select <strong>Internet Protocol Version 4</strong> (or Version 6 if desired).
      li Click <strong>Properties</strong>.
      li Write down any existing DNS server entries for future reference.
      li Click <strong>Use The Following DNS Server Addresses</strong>.
      li
        span Replace those addresses with the 1.1.1.1 DNS addresses:
        ul
          li For IPv4: <strong>1.1.1.1</strong> and/or <strong>1.0.0.1</strong>
          li For IPv6: <strong>2606:4700:4700::1111</strong> and <strong>2606:4700:4700::1001</strong>

      li Click <strong>OK</strong>, then <strong>Close</strong>.
      li Restart your browser.
      li You‚Äôre all set! Your device now has faster, more private DNS servers üöÄ

  .instructions(data-platform="android")
    .message
      p.collapsed-margins.message-content
        | Note that Android requires a static IP to use custom DNS servers.
        | This setup requires additional setup on your router, affecting your network‚Äôs strategy for adding new devices to the network.
        | We recommend configuring your <button class="inline-button" type="button" onclick="chooseInstructions('router')">router‚Äôs DNS</button> instead.
        | This will give all devices on your network the full speed and privacy benefits of 1.1.1.1 DNS.
    ol
      li From your Android‚Äôs app list, open the <strong>Settings</strong> app.
      li Under the <strong>Wireless & networks</strong> section, tap <strong>Wi-Fi</strong>,
      li Long press your preferred network in the list until a context menu appears.
      li Tap the <strong>Modify network</strong>, then tap <strong>Advanced options</strong>.
      li Tap <strong>Advanced options</strong>, then tap <strong>IP Settings</strong>.
      li Change <strong>Dynamic</strong> to <strong>Static</strong>.
      li Using your router‚Äôs configuration, enter your device‚Äôs IP address and gateway.
      li Tap the <strong>DNS</strong> field, then erase the number in the field.
      li In the <strong>DNS 1</strong> field, enter <strong>1.1.1.1</strong>
      li In the <strong>DNS 2</strong> field, enter <strong>1.0.0.1</strong>
      li In the <strong>DNS 3</strong> field, enter <strong>2606:4700:4700::1111</strong>
      li In the <strong>DNS 4</strong> field, enter <strong>2606:4700:4700::1001</strong> 
      li Tap <strong>Save</strong>.

      li You‚Äôre all set! Your device now has faster, more private DNS servers üöÄ

  .instructions(data-platform="router")
    .message.center
      p.collapsed-margins.message-content
        | Your router‚Äôs configuration may vary. Consult your manual for more information.

    ol
      li Connect to your preferred wireless network.
      li Enter your router‚Äôs gateway IP address in your browser.
      li If prompted, fill in your username and password. This information may be labeled on the router.
      li In your router‚Äôs configuration page, locate the <strong>DNS server</strong> settings.
      li Write down any existing DNS server entries for future reference.
      li
        span Replace those addresses with the 1.1.1.1 DNS addresses:
        ul
          li For IPv4: <strong>1.1.1.1</strong> and/or <strong>1.0.0.1</strong>
          li For IPv6: <strong>2606:4700:4700::1111</strong> and <strong>2606:4700:4700::1001</strong>
      li Save your settings, then restart your browser.
      li You‚Äôre all set! Your device now has faster, more private DNS servers üöÄ
